claim: The House of Lusignan was a royal house of Russian origin.
premise_source_doc_sentence: The Château de Lusignan  (  in Lusignan , Vienne département , France  )  was the ancestral seat of the House of Lusignan , Poitevin Marcher Lords , who distinguished themselves in the First Crusade and became the royal family of the Kingdom of Jerusalem , the Kingdom of Cyprus , and the Armenian Kingdom of Cilicia .
